history.content: I took 168 on Fall 18 and it was a great course! I think it is useful from a design a system perspective or if you are interested on learning how the internet works. I wouldn't necessarily say it's useful for software app development, I would recommend 160 or 169 for that, but 168 is a good choice if you want to learn without being under a very high workload. When I took the course it had 2 midterms, 2 projects and a final. The projects were very straightforward if you went to lecture and understood the class concepts, while the midterms and final were generally a mix of "do you recall this" and real-life applications of class concepts

Hi, I will be taking cs168 during the spring 2020 and I was wondering if this class is useful for someone who sees himself as a software app developer. I need to take a "lightweight" class and rumors say this is one of them. I read that this class is at pair or easier than D100. What do you think or what alternatives do you recommend. 

Courses taken: cs61 series, ee16 series, cs70/170, cs186, d100.
history.subject: cs168 workload and usefulness advice for a senior.
